    pages = "1-5",
    abstract = "Effective communication is one of the main challenges for children with Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD), especially for those with limited verbal and non-verbal skills. This difficulty directly affects their social, emotional, and educational development. In recent years, artificial intelligence has begun to play a key role in inclusive educational environments by facilitating more accessible learning experiences tailored to individual needs. In this context, OpenAI’s GPT-4 model represents a significant advancement, as it combines natural language understanding with visual analysis, enabling a richer and more contextualized multimodal interaction. This technology can provide personalized responses, adaptive tutoring, and real-time multimedia support, which is especially beneficial for children with ASD by offering a flexible tool that complements traditional therapeutic and educational interventions. Its integration into specialized applications opens new possibilities for promoting the communicative and cognitive development of this population.",
    keywords = "Autism;Visualization;Adaptation models;Image recognition;Learning (artificial intelligence);Real-time systems;Natural language processing;Mobile applications;Monitoring;Testing;Autism Spectrum Disorder;ASD;augmentative communication;PECS;mobile application;image recognition;artificial intelligence;GPT-4",
    doi = "10.1109/ICACIT66767.2025.11369559",
